Exam Timer System
A web-based countdown timer system for managing multiple exam timers in an invigilation setting. Designed to allow flexible setup, start, and monitoring of multiple exam durations. Built with HTML, CSS, and JavaScript.

Features
Venue Display: Set and display the exam venue name.
Multiple Timers: Add multiple timers with custom module codes and durations.
Central Start Button: Start all timers at once with a single button click.
Flexible Timer Management: Remove individual timers as needed.
Fullscreen Mode: Toggle fullscreen mode for an unobstructed view.
Warning Indicators: Red warning color appears when timers reach the final 5 minutes.
Auto-Stopping: Timers visually mark when they reach zero.
Demo

Installation
Clone this repository:

bash
Copy code
git clone https://github.com/your-username/exam-timer-system.git
cd exam-timer-system
Open index.html in a web browser.

Usage
Set the Venue Name by typing in the input box and clicking Set Venue.
Add timers by entering the Module Code, Hours, and Minutes and clicking Add Timer.
Once all timers are set, click START ALL TIMERS at the bottom to begin all countdowns.
Individual timers can be removed using the Remove button.
Toggle fullscreen mode using the Fullscreen button at the top-right.
